			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="111854176738888493"></a> 
				Orcmid, I really appreciate your painstaking effort to untangle this web and clarify what might work. However, even if necessary, it just makes my head hurt to try to think this through. Examples of open source programs and applications that managed to satisfy the directives and constraints you describe would be extremely helpful.<BR/><BR/>And on another topic: couldn't I just use a CreativeCommons license for my software? What do the other OSS licences provide? Is it the use at your own risk and don't blame me for problems clause?<br />
				<div class="byline">
                  <a href="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/blog/2005/06/heavy-lifting-toward-open-formats-in.asp#111854176738888493" 
                     title="permanent link">#</a> 
                  posted by <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3342052">Bill Anderson</a>: 
